          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TELES",
                "SI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The telescope consisted of two silicon",
                "counters, a 292-mu-m deltaE counter and a 3-mm E",
                "counter, and was used for detecting reaction products",
                "emitted at forward angles. The E+deltaE energy scale",
                "was calibrated by observation of the elastically",
                "scattered alpha particles and recoil 3He at several",
                "angles out to 38 degrees. The proton spectra at",
                "backward angles were obtained with a fully depleted",
                "500-mu-m silicon detector about 21.6 cm from the",
                "center of the chamber. The energy scale was",
                "calibrated by alpha particles from the decay of a",
                "244Cm source."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The 3He gas, usually at a pressure of about 100 Torr,",
                "was contained by a 1.8-mg/cm2 foil of type-H Kapton",
                "glued to the outside of the cylinder."
              ]
            }
